node.text:
Reposted from @gisbarbados The Ministry of Health and Wellness is urging persons who have frequented bars in the Nelson Street, Wellington Street, and Suttle Street areas, as well as on the Spring Garden Highway within the last two weeks, as well as individuals who have been in close contact with such persons, to get tested for COVID-19.

This appeal is based on information reaching the Ministry that several of these establishments are associated with a recent cluster of COVID-19 cases.

Tomorrow, Monday, August 2, and Tuesday, August 3, persons can go to the Wildey Gymnasium Testing site; the Eunice Gibson Polyclinic, Warrens, St. Michael;  and the Branford Taitt Polyclinic, Black Rock, St. Michael,  from 8:00 a.m to noon.

After the bank holidays,  the main testing site at the Wildey Gymnasium will be open Monday to Saturday, from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m., and Sunday from 9:00 a.m. until 1:00 p.m. ; while, the Eunice Gibson and  Branford Taitt Polyclinics will be open from 8:30 a.m. until 4:00 p.m. 

#importantnotice
#covid19
#covidtesting
